en katalanischer Jugendlicher der Sprache in Jugendsendungen und -publikationen in katalanischen Kommunikationsmedien gegenüber.  aYouth media present socio-cultural tendencies which young people reflect in their language and thus often set linguistic trends. Or does it work the other way round? In either case, there is a close connection between youth culture and youth language, which in Catalonia is heightened by the encounter between two languages and cultures, Spanish and Catalan. Against his background, the author contrasts and compares linguistic products of young Catalans with the language used in youth broadcasts and publications in Catalan communication media.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCatalan languagexSlang. 0aLanguage and culturezSpainzBarcelona. 0aMass media and languagezSpainzBarcelona. 0aYouthzSpainzBarcelonaxLanguage. 4aJugendsprache. 4aKatalanisch. 4aSoziolinguistik. 4aVarietätenlinguistik. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / Spanish.2bisacsh  aCatalan.  aSociolinguistics.  aVarieties of Language (Catalan).  aYouth Language.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2008z9783110209457oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978348452345640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978348497047240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783484970472423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783484970472/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2008  aZDB-23-D